<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 11102 requires that a United States vessel on a foreign or intercoastal domestic voyage be equipped with a medicine chest, and provides a penalty for noncompliance. The Committee intends that regulation will provide for a well stocked medicine chest adequate for the crew of a vessel.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf68fe41a-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf68fe41b-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1996—Subsec. (a). <ref href="/us/pl/104/324">Pub. L. 104–324</ref> inserted “as measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14502">section 14502 of this title</ref>, or an alternate tonnage measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14302">section 14302 of this title</ref> as prescribed by the Secretary under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14104">section 14104 of this title</ref>” after “75 gross tons”.</p>
</note>
